article.headline: Oakland, Mich. 99, UMKC 62
article.story: OAKLAND, Mich. -- Keith Benson had 20 points and 10 rebounds to lead five Oakland players in double-figure scoring in the Golden Grizzlies' 99-62 victory against UMKC on Saturday night. Will Hudson scored 17 points, Reggie Hamilton 16, Ledrick Eackles 11 and Larry Wright 10 for Oakland (5-3, 2-0 Summit League), which won its 22nd straight home game against a conference foe. Wright had 11 rebounds. Spencer Johnson had 19 points and 13 rebounds and Trinity Hall 13 points for UMKC (4-3, 0-2), which shot 34.9 percent (22 of 63) from the floor. Greg Kampe, Oakland's 27th-year coach, earned his 450th career victory. The Golden Grizzlies scored the game's first 10 points, and another 10-0 run later in the first half extended their lead to 42-18. Oakland was up 60-27 at halftime and led by 43 points in the second half.
